# Rust Conventions

## Error Handling

```rust
// ❌ BAD: Swallowed Result
let _ = do_thing();

// ✅ GOOD: Explicit handling or documented ignore
do_thing().map_err(|e| tracing::error!(%e, "do_thing failed"))?;
// Or: let _ = do_thing(); // Intentional: fire-and-forget background task
```

- Use `Result<T, AosError>`; see `crates/adapteros-core/src/error.rs`.
- New error conditions need codes in `error_codes.rs`.

## SSE Event Contract

- Server SSE events in `streaming_infer.rs` and UI `InferenceEvent` in `signals/chat.rs` must stay in sync.
- New UI event fields must use `#[serde(default)]` for backward compatibility.
- When adding fields to SSE events, update corresponding Playwright SSE helpers and mocks in `tests/playwright/`.

## Error Code Governance

- Canonical source: `crates/adapteros-core/src/error_codes.rs`.
- Do not introduce new raw string literal error codes in handlers.
- Prefer canonical constants or canonicalization helper paths:
  - `crates/adapteros-server-api/src/error_code_normalization.rs`
  - `crates/adapteros-server-api/src/api_error.rs`
- Run `bash scripts/check_error_code_drift.sh` after error-path changes.

## Logging

- Prefer `tracing` macros over `println!`.
- See `docs/ERRORS.md` for standards.

## Determinism (when touching routing/seeding)

- Seed derivation: HKDF-SHA256 with B3 global seed (`adapteros-core/src/seed.rs`).
- Router tie-break: score DESC, stable_id ASC; Q15 denom = 32767.0 (`adapteros-lora-router/src/quantization.rs`).
- No `-ffast-math` flags (CI scans for this).
- Set `AOS_DEBUG_DETERMINISM=1` to log seed/router details.

## Build & Test

- `cargo fmt --all` before commit.
- `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings`.
- Targeted tests: `cargo test -p <crate>`; determinism: `cargo test --test determinism_core_suite`.
